comments.text: Around Christmas 1979, I built one of every Airfix OO kit we had in the hobby shop I worked part-time for in Northern California. Although their specialty was (and still is) Lionel toy trains and their ilk, we served the model train hobbyist. Though just static models, the display turned out rather well, and helped sales. Just like cardstock buildings, which go back eighty? years, properly placed static models really add to the layout. It is one of the reasons I look through junk boxes at train meets. Some of that junk can turn out to be real diamonds in the rough. The additions look great. A model railroad is never finished, just done for now.
comments.author: @manthony1956
